Subject: [PATCH] feat: add ErrorBoundary around report / articles / timeline
 views
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A malformed report JSON, broken story shape, or any uncaught render
exception in a child component currently takes down the entire page.
Wrap the main content regions in an ErrorBoundary so one bad section
shows a recoverable error message instead of a white screen.

- New ErrorBoundary class component accepts `label`, `fallback`, and
  `resetKey`. When `resetKey` changes (date, edition, tab) the boundary
  clears its error state automatically so switching context is enough
  to retry.
- BroadcastHero is wrapped with fallback={null} — if it crashes, the
  hero silently disappears and the rest of the app keeps working.
- The analysis section, ArticlesView, and TimelineView each get their
  own boundary with a friendly fallback.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
